  "text": "anchor Image: André Nazareth Located in Rio de Janeiro, a new compact leisure annex has taken shape at the site of an original Oscar Niemeyer house. Designed by firm Siqueira + Azul Arquitetura, the project was formed through the acquisition of the next-door property, resulting in an expansion of the existing residence. Image: André NazarethImage: Ruy TeixeiraCalled Itaúna House, the approximately 8,611-square-foot annex appears to hover between the pool and garden. It was developed as three independent constructions and is fully interconnected by pathways, walkways, and stairs. Image: André NazarethImage: André NazarethThe façades of the main existing blocks feature large pivoting panels, allowing for a seamless transition between the indoor and outdoor spaces. These function through a custom structural scheme in an iron square mesh. Image: André NazarethThe project also features a circular oculus that provides views to the courtyard, while inviting natural light inside. The annex is crowned by a tower element with large sliding glass panels. This is accessed by a distinctive helical staircase. Image: André NazarethImage: André NazarethItaúna House is composed of natural materials, such as stone and concrete, which highlight contrasts while maintaining aesthetic continuity throughout the home. Image: André Nazareth",
  "image": "https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa5c22772b1810bfc07f7687f0ee029.jpeg?fit=crop\u0026auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026enlarge=true\u0026crop=faces\u0026w=1200\u0026h=707",
  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa5c22772b1810bfc07f7687f0ee029.jpeg?auto=compress%2Cformat\" title=\"Image: André Nazareth\" data-size=\"5719x3813\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa5c22772b1810bfc07f7687f0ee029.jpeg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa5c22772b1810bfc07f7687f0ee029.jpeg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa5c22772b1810bfc07f7687f0ee029.jpeg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa5c22772b1810bfc07f7687f0ee029.jpeg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" title=\"Image: André Nazareth\" alt=\"Image: André Nazareth\" width=\"514\" height=\"\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eImage: André Nazareth\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eLocated in \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/15446/rio-de-janeiro\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRio de Janeiro\u003c/a\u003e, a new compact leisure annex has taken shape at the site of an original \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/4595/oscar-niemeyer/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eOscar Niemeyer\u003c/a\u003e house. Designed by firm Siqueira + Azul Arquitetura, the project was formed through the acquisition of the next-door property, resulting in an expansion of the existing \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/460574/residential-architecture\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eresidence\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/7a/7a992766a2c9ebaae46b2073e0b39552.jpeg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/7a/7a992766a2c9ebaae46b2073e0b39552.jpeg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/7a/7a992766a2c9ebaae46b2073e0b39552.jpeg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/7a/7a992766a2c9ebaae46b2073e0b39552.jpeg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/7a/7a992766a2c9ebaae46b2073e0b39552.jpeg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: André Nazareth\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e4/e401e31700695c1f44040bad8e487ef4.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e4/e401e31700695c1f44040bad8e487ef4.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e4/e401e31700695c1f44040bad8e487ef4.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e4/e401e31700695c1f44040bad8e487ef4.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e4/e401e31700695c1f44040bad8e487ef4.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Ruy Teixeira\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eCalled Itaúna House, the approximately 8,611-square-foot annex appears to hover between the pool and garden. It was developed as three independent constructions and is fully interconnected by pathways, walkways, and stairs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e6/e6188e9c42b1145f25233afbb29e2324.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e6/e6188e9c42b1145f25233afbb29e2324.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e6/e6188e9c42b1145f25233afbb29e2324.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e6/e6188e9c42b1145f25233afbb29e2324.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/e6/e6188e9c42b1145f25233afbb29e2324.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: André Nazareth\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/99/99b43d8c70522124b5cbba7f3998810a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1542\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/99/99b43d8c70522124b5cbba7f3998810a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/99/99b43d8c70522124b5cbba7f3998810a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/99/99b43d8c70522124b5cbba7f3998810a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/99/99b43d8c70522124b5cbba7f3998810a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: André Nazareth\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe façades of the main existing blocks feature large pivoting panels, allowing for a seamless transition between the indoor and outdoor spaces. These function through a custom structural scheme in an iron square mesh.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/17/177f0deb637907ffaaf64b2426e7dbbf.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/17/177f0deb637907ffaaf64b2426e7dbbf.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/17/177f0deb637907ffaaf64b2426e7dbbf.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/17/177f0deb637907ffaaf64b2426e7dbbf.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/17/177f0deb637907ffaaf64b2426e7dbbf.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: André Nazareth\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe project also features a circular oculus that provides views to the courtyard, while inviting natural light inside. The annex is crowned by a tower element with large sliding glass panels. This is accessed by a distinctive helical staircase.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/00/00a71eb8d2dc7ef8f91623888cb606c2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\